# tests/corpus/ fixtures represent real document content used for
# byte-for-byte round-trip tests (e.g. tests/unit/io/test_open_read.py).
# Without this, Git's line-ending normalization is governed entirely by
# each checkout machine's local core.autocrlf default, which differs
# between Windows and macOS/Linux CI runners -- the same committed file
# can check out with different bytes on different platforms, defeating
# the whole point of a byte-identical fixture. -text disables any EOL
# conversion so every checkout gets the exact bytes that were committed.
tests/corpus/** -text
